---

**Summary of gaps by severity:**

| Gap | Severity | Why |
|-----|----------|-----|
| `roundToTwo` untested | Medium | Exported; used in all rounding paths |
| User with scores but no stats excluded silently | High | Surprising contract — data loss if Firestore write order varies |
| Duplicate `(uid, gameId)` rows → last wins | High | Potential silent scoring bug if scoreRows aren't deduplicated upstream |
| User with stats but no scores | Medium | Valid state after data migration or partial writes |
| `computeCompositeScore` with zeros | Low | Defensive; formula produces 0 but worth pinning |
| `aggregateGameLeaderboard` empty/no-match | Low | Defensive; easy regression target |

The two **High** items (scores-without-stats exclusion and duplicate row overwrite) are worth the most attention — they describe behavioral contracts that aren't obvious from the function signatures and could silently produce wrong leaderboard results.

